s_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-20T10:43:00Z","updated_at":"2020-07-20T10:43:00Z","body":"While I think it might be possible for an alternate K/V store to support what you want, I don't know of any that actually do.\r\n\r\nAs I said earlier, Bleve was designed with the assumption that only a single process could directly access the index.  It's fair to criticize that assumption, but it doesn't change the reality at the moment.  The alternatives I'm aware of are to use inter-process-communication to access the index from other processes, or to only open the indexes for writing briefly, then close and copy them for the other processes to query.\r\n\r\nLonger-term this can be fixed in bleve/scorch.  I have an experimental new library that does locking at the individual file level, allowing multiple read processes at the same time as a single writer process, but this code won't be release for several more months.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/comments/660950890/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"mschoch","id":298143,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5ODE0Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/298143?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch","html_url":"https://github.com/mschoch","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/comments/661036796","html_url":"https://github.com/blevesearch/bleve/issues/405#issuecomment-661036796","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/405","id":661036796,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2MTAzNjc5Ng==","user":{"login":"Losses","id":1384036,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzODQwMzY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1384036?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses","html_url":"https://github.com/Losses","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-20T13:23:33Z","updated_at":"2020-07-20T13:23:33Z","body":"> While I think it might be possible for an alternate K/V store to support what you want, I don't know of any that actually do.\r\n> \r\n> As I said earlier, Bleve was designed with the assumption that only a single process could directly access the index. It's fair to criticize that assumption, but it doesn't change the reality at the moment. The alternatives I'm aware of are to use inter-process-communication to access the index from other processes, or to only open the indexes for writing briefly, then close and copy them for the other processes to query.\r\n> \r\n> Longer-term this can be fixed in bleve/scorch. I have an experimental new library that does locking at the individual file level, allowing multiple read processes at the same time as a single writer process, but this code won't be release for several more months.\r\n\r\nYeah, thanks for you precious insight, there're a lot of trade off while designing a program so there's nothing should be criticized, I'll try to find a way to achieve what we need, try my best.\r\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/comments/661036796/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Losses","id":1384036,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzODQwMzY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1384036?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses","html_url":"https://github.com/Losses","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Losses/repos",